cves.description: Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information vulnerability in Mitsubishi Electric Corporation MELSEC iQ-F Series CPU module allows a remote unauthenticated attacker to obtain credential information by intercepting SLMP communication messages, and read or write the device values of the product and stop the operations of programs by using the obtained credential information.
problemType: CWE-319 Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information

cves.description: Missing Authentication for Critical Function vulnerability in Mitsubishi Electric Corporation MELSEC iQ-F Series CPU module allows a remote unauthenticated attacker to read or write the device values of the product and stop the operation of the programs, since MODBUS/TCP in the products does not have authentication features.
problemType: CWE-306 Missing Authentication for Critical Function

cves.description: The eHRD CTMS developed by Sunnet has an Arbitrary File Reading vulnerability, allowing remote attackers with administrator privileges to exploit Relative Path Traversal to download arbitrary system files.
Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key vulnerability in Akinsoft ProKuafor allows Resource Leak Exposure.This issue affects ProKuafor: from s1.02.07 before v1.02.08.
problemType: CWE-639 Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key

cves.description: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation (XSS or 'Cross-site Scripting') vulnerability in Akinsoft ProKuaför allows Cross-Site Scripting (XSS).This issue affects ProKuaför: from s1.02.07 before v1.02.08.
problemType: CWE-79 Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation (XSS or 'Cross-site Scripting')

cves.description: A User enumeration vulnerability in the /CredentialsServlet/ForgotPassword endpoint in Silverpeas 6.4.1 and 6.4.2 allows remote attackers to determine valid usernames via the Login parameter.
Delta Electronics DIAView has an authentication bypass vulnerability.
problemType: CWE-306 Missing Authentication for Critical Function

cves.description: A vulnerability in the h2oai/h2o-3 repository allows attackers to exploit deserialization of untrusted data, potentially leading to arbitrary code execution and reading of system files. This issue affects the latest master branch version 3.47.0.99999. The vulnerability arises from the ability to bypass regular expression filters intended to prevent malicious parameter injection in JDBC connections. Attackers can manipulate spaces between parameters to evade detection, allowing for unauthorized file access and code execution. The vulnerability is addressed in version 3.46.0.8.
